places.name: Layou River Area
places.perex: Check that you are coming in the good season when waters are low and peaceful for swimming. Very popular for playful and sportive activities!

places.name: Trafalgar Falls
places.perex: Walk only four hundred metres from Papillote Wilderness Retreat, near village of Trafalgar, to the spectacular and impressive waterfalls.

places.name: Mero Beach
places.perex: Grey-sandy beach with restaurant and snack services is a popular spot for families. Calm and safe, romantic sunsets.

places.name: Hampstead Beach
places.perex: What an exception -the sand is coloured black. But don't worry.

places.name: Morne Aux Diables
places.perex: Go for an excellent but very demanding hike on this mountain located in the very north of the island. It often gets pretty cloudy.

places.name: Amazona imperialis
places.perex: El loro imperial o amazona imperial es un ave de la familia Psittacidae de plumaje verde y púrpura.

places.name: Morne Bruce Viewpoint
places.perex: For splendid views of Roseau and the sea, walk up the hill. You will be charmed away by the picturesque scenery.

places.name: Victoria Falls
places.perex: Undertaking a medium-difficult hike, you will reach utterly striking waterfalls which attract a lot of tourist attention.

places.name: Main Market
places.perex: Another great spot for a good bargain. Fresh vegetables and fruit from local farmers are sold here, along with fish.

places.name: Portsmouth Market
places.perex: Whether you need to satisfy your craving for a walk or just want to kill some time shopping, pop in here. Use your haggling skills.

places.name: Screw's Sulphur Spa
places.perex: Highlight: a trip to hot water spring spa with little waterfalls. Haven of tranquility.

places.name: Indian River
places.perex: The Indian River is a river on the Caribbean island of Dominica. It flows to the Caribbean Sea between the town of Portsmouth and the…

places.perex: The Carib Territory, also known as the Carib Reserve or Kalinago Territory, is a 3,700-acre district in the Caribbean island-nation of…

places.name: P.A.Y.S - Portsmouth Association of Yacht Services
All Saints University School of Medicine
All Saints University School of Medicine
Titou Gorge
places.perex: Titou stands for 'little throat'. And indeed this tiny gorge with a lake resembles it.

places.name: Rodney's Rock
places.perex: This place has a unique and dramatic undersea world. Very rich and ready to be explored by you.

places.name: Soltoun Falls
places.perex: To access these pretty much unknown waterfalls, you have to pay five dollars. But it's worth it considering the plentiful of waterfalls.

places.name: Spanny Falls
places.perex: Who would say that these two teeny waterfalls would be so cold! Eeeeh!

places.name: Cabrits Dive Centre
places.perex: Scuba-diving, snorkelling, yachting, coastal cruises and much more. A bit tricky to get there, so read the instructions on the website.

places.name: Carib Indian Model Village
places.perex: Fascinating wonderland of the ancient Indian traditions of indigenous people of Dominica. Learn about their history, habits and daily life.

places.name: Ti Kwen Glo Cho - Hot Springs
places.perex: Emerging from the earth, these seductive hot springs will definitely make you spend all day here. Just idle away your time!

places.name: Wotton Waven
places.perex: The small village has lots to offer. The start-off for many hiking tours, hot springs destination and hotel concentration makes it popular!

places.name: Middleham Falls
places.perex: You have to undergo a one hour trek throughout the rainforest to reach these celestial waterfalls. Be careful with your cam here.

places.name: Roseau Historical District
places.perex: Stroll down the busy streets which remember the days of 17th century. Some examples of fine Victorian architecture are to be found here.

places.name: Emerald Pool
places.perex: The tropical wet sultry climate, cooling water and a beautiful waterfall make up the atmosphere of this romantic grotto.

places.name: Papillote Wilderness Retreat
places.perex: This sanctuary for your soul is an ideal place to get away from busy every day life. Just spa, nature and tranquility.

places.name: Champagne Reef
places.perex: Explore this fine diving destination. Best at night. Because you might see some creepy huge creatures.

places.name: Secret Beach
places.perex: Only for adventurers and fools. To get to this secluded hidden beach, you must climb down the cliff.

places.name: Rain Forest Aerial Tram
places.perex: Almost an adrenaline experience to be sitting in the gondola and passing the treetops of the tallest rainforest trees! This is a stunner!

places.name: Chaudiere Pool
places.perex: Except for the rainy season, the hike to this veritably magnificent little pool is easy. After rains, it gets dangerous!

places.name: Valley of Desolation
places.perex: This area seems to be abandoned not only by people but by nature itself. The lunar landscape with evergreen emerging gases is spectacular!

places.name: Jaco Flats
places.perex: It's the place to seen! Escaped slaves cut their way through the rainforests.

places.name: Roseau Public Library
places.perex: The library is also an active commune centre where people gather to participate the exhibitions and lectures on various topics.

places.name: Morne Diablotins
places.perex: Almost sounds diabolic. The trail up to the highest peak of the island could be described as such. Guide is required.

places.name: Perdu Temps Trail
places.perex: In translation Lost in Time... you might also get a little lost, being tired after undertaking this challenging trail.

places.name: Alliance Française de la Dominique
places.perex: This institute representing France all over the world is often a vibrant and dynamic cultural centre. Expositions and exhibitions.

places.name: Pointe Guignard
places.perex: Quite an exceptional place to dive in. It might get a bit tricky to get to the fifty feet cave but once in, you will be in awe!

places.name: Imperial Road
places.perex: As the adjective describes, the road is truly magnificent. Crooked, winding, sometimes muddy... but offers great viewpoints!

places.name: L'Or River
places.perex: Take off your clothes and jump straight into this five-star natural swimming pool. It's deep enough, so enjoy.

places.name: Northern Forest Reserve
places.perex: One of three park reserves in Dominica that features the Carribean tropical fauna and flora. Less explored and less touristy.

places.name: Soufriere Sulphur Springs
places.perex: The ever-present sulphur fumes have banished most of the living organisms. A pool has been built, using the warmth of the springs.

places.name: White River
places.perex: Named after its milky-white colour, this river runs down the island and reaches the sea at Pointe Mulatte Bay.

places.name: Dangleben's Pinnacles
places.perex: Top diving destination! The five pinnacles are home to hundreds of thousands of fish. See for yourself.

places.name: Northern Link Road
places.perex: Panoramic road which takes you through the north of the island gives you some majestic views of Guadalupe and other islands.

places.name: Roseau Valley
places.perex: Trafalgar, Laudat and Wotten Waven are the main settlements of this valley which has countless accommodation options and natural gems.

places.name: Chemin Letang Trail
places.perex: It used to be the only possible way from the east to the west of the island. Take the lake trail which will lead across to Boeri lake.

places.name: Freshwater Lake
places.perex: Having reached the lake, you can decide whether you will want to go on a boat tour, do kayaking or simply walk around.

places.name: Fort Shirley
places.perex: The presence of the British colonial history can be seen in the fort. Although it does not serve its former purpose any more.

places.name: Sunsets
places.perex: Anywhere on the western side of island, the sun sets down and makes a million-dollar romantic sceneries. Take your sweetie for a walk!

places.name: Grand Bay
places.perex: This ancient village was already inhabited 2000 years ago. Nestled in a great bay, the surrounding landscape makes it a perfect holiday spot!

places.name: Scotts Head
places.perex: A real diver's paradise where the undersea world opens to you fully and you are emerged into colourful lively home to thousands of fish.

places.name: Woodford Hill Beach
places.perex: This beach belongs to the most popular attractions in Dominica. Expect it to be a bit crowded in the peak season.

places.name: Milton (Syndicate) Falls
places.perex: Nothing to do in the afternoon? Then why not see another waterfall.

places.name: Glassy Trail
places.perex: Easy one hour hike for everyone, children included. You will see unexpectedly much in such a short time.

places.name: Fond St. Jean
places.perex: Tiny unshowy village where fishing is the main source of livehood. Meet the locals and chat with them.

places.name: Du Mas Lake
places.perex: Early in the morning the lake draws animals to drink here and wash themselves. You might witness some of them if you are an early-bird.

places.name: Gallion Viewpoint
places.perex: Who says that small is not interesting is wrong. This village proves it.

places.name: Soufriere Bay
places.perex: The almost forgotten village of Soufriere prides itself on the long beach, popular mainly with scuba-divers.

places.name: Sari-Sari Waterfall
places.perex: Very impressive scene opens to you after a long hike when you reach the open space where this waterfall scatters on the stones.

places.name: Boeri Lake
places.perex: Located in a hazy rainforest at high altitude, the lake is encompassed by legends and myths. Hope you won't meet the Nessie-like monster!

places.name: Benjamin Park
places.perex: In a little lazy mood? Then nip across the road to the charming green municipal park.

places.name: Isulukati Waterfall
places.perex: Splendid shallow pool with small waterfalls. Ideal for family bathing and playful games!

places.name: L'Escalier Tete Chien
places.perex: Volcano fell in love with the sea and touched it by its finger. The rock descending into the sea is a favourite and depicted in legends.

places.name: Soufriere-Scotts Head Marine Reserve
places.perex: Passionate divers will have the time of their life in this marine reserve. The underwater world around the extinct volcanic crater is great!

places.name: Petite Soufriere - Rosalie Trail
places.perex: If you are not too much of a hiker but you still want to see the Dominican nature, you can take this easy four hour trail. Spectacular views!

places.name: Morne Anglais
places.perex: Quite a demanding hike up one of the tallest Dominican mountains. You will come across stunning views.

places.name: Tete Morne
places.perex: Continuing from the Sulphur Springs you can follow the trail which will lead you to the village overlooking Soufriere.

places.name: Toucari Bay
places.perex: Interesting not only for its serenity and latency but also for the shipwreck off the bay which supposedly was a First World War German ship.

places.name: Londonderry Beach
places.perex: Long sandy beach with palm trees under which you might realize the true meaning of life. Nice meditation spot.

places.name: Massacre
places.perex: What a weird name for a village, don't you think? Indeed, named after a massacre done by the British in 17th century.
